<div class="max-w-7xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8 py-8">
  <h1 class="text-3xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-8">âš¡ Performance Comparison</h1>
  
  <div class="bg-white rounded-lg shadow p-6 mb-6">
    <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold mb-4">PostgreSQL vs ClickHouse</h2>
    <p class="text-gray-600 mb-6">
      Comparing query performance between PostgreSQL (transactional database) and ClickHouse (analytics database).
    </p>
    
    <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 gap-6 mb-8">
      <div class="border rounded-lg p-4">
        <h3 class="font-semibold text-gray-700 mb-2">ðŸ“Š Database Sizes</h3>
        <div class="space-y-2">
          <div class="flex justify-between">
            <span class="text-gray-600">PostgreSQL:</span>
            <span class="font-mono font-semibold"><%= @pg_size %></span>
          </div>
          <div class="flex justify-between">
            <span class="text-gray-600">ClickHouse:</span>
            <span class="font-mono font-semibold"><%= @ch_size %></span>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
      
      <div class="border rounded-lg p-4">
        <h3 class="font-semibold text-gray-700 mb-2">ðŸ“ˆ Data Volume</h3>
        <div class="space-y-2">
          <div class="flex justify-between">
            <span class="text-gray-600">Channels:</span>
            <span class="font-mono font-semibold"><%= Channel.count %></span>
          </div>
          <div class="flex justify-between">
            <span class="text-gray-600">Posts:</span>
            <span class="font-mono font-semibold"><%= Post.count %></span>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
    
    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold mb-4">Query Performance</h3>
    
    <% @benchmarks.each do |query_name, result| %>
      <div class="border-l-4 border-indigo-500 bg-gray-50 p-4 mb-4">
        <h4 class="font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-3"><%= query_name.to_s.titleize %></h4>
        
        <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-3 gap-4">
          <div>
            <div class="text-sm text-gray-600">PostgreSQL</div>
            <div class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900">
              <%= (result[:postgresql][:time] * 1000).round(2) %>ms
            </div>
          </div>
          
          <div>
            <div class="text-sm text-gray-600">ClickHouse</div>
            <div class="text-2xl font-bold text-green-600">
              <%= (result[:clickhouse][:time] * 1000).round(2) %>ms
            </div>
          </div>
          
          <div>
            <div class="text-sm text-gray-600">Speedup</div>
            <div class="text-2xl font-bold text-indigo-600">
              <%= result[:speedup] %>x faster
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
        
        <div class="mt-3">
          <div class="w-full bg-gray-200 rounded-full h-2">
            <div class="bg-green-500 h-2 rounded-full" 
                 style="width: <%= [100 / result[:speedup], 100].min %>%"></div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    <% end %>
  </div>
  
  <div class="bg-blue-50 border border-blue-200 rounded-lg p-6">
    <h3 class="font-semibold text-blue-900 mb-2">ðŸ’¡ Key Takeaways</h3>
    <ul class="list-disc list-inside space-y-1 text-blue-800">
      <li>ClickHouse is optimized for analytical queries (aggregations, time-series)</li>
      <li>PostgreSQL is better for transactional operations (CRUD)</li>
      <li>Use ClickHouse for dashboards and reports</li>
      <li>Use PostgreSQL for user data and real-time updates</li>
      <li>Data syncs every 10 minutes automatically</li>
    </ul>
  </div>
  
  <%= link_to "â† Back to Dashboard", dashboard_path, class: "mt-6 inline-block text-indigo-600 hover:text-indigo-800" %>
</div>
